Scope Note: Theban Tomb (TT) 320 is located next to Deir el-Bahari in the Theban necropolis and contained an extraordinary cache of mummified remains and funeral equipment of more than 50 kings, queens, royals and their nobility. The tomb may have originally belonged to the High Priest of Amun Pinedjem II, his wife Nesikhons and other close family members. At the time of Pinudjem’s death around 969 BC, mummies from former dynasties that were vulnerable to grave robbers were moved that in a collective efforts to protect them.
